


static=>can not apply top , left , right , bottom

positions
absolute = apply top , left , right , bottom
relative=apply top , left , right , bottom
sticky=apply top , left , right , bottom
fixed=apply top , left , right , bottom


absolute
1.apply top , left , right , bottom
2.remove space from the DOM
3.it will change the behaviour , ie., it converts to inline from block
4. it takes parent as a reference only when parent must be having one position other than static


relative
1.apply top , left , right , bottom
2.it won't remove space from the dom
3.it will not change it's behaviour
4.it will take current position as a reference

fixed
1.apply top , left , right , bottom
2.remove space from the DOM
3.it will change the behaviour , ie., it converts to inline from block
4.it will take viewport or visibility area as reference

sticky
1.apply top , left , right , bottom
2.it won't remove space from the dom
3.it will not change it's behaviour
4.it will take viewport or visibility area as reference

